{"tid":2076839,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"美國眾議員: 天安門危機逼近香港，呼籲救到幾多港人得幾多","createTime":"2020-06-24T00:30:58.000Z","updateTime":"2020-06-24T01:00:22.000Z","uid":305299,"like":18,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"b4ddf0922544517dcb769bf99d421ea99d5c1474","tid":2076839,"uid":305299,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T00:30:58.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/4T5bfK1.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2F4T5bfK1.jpg&h=639cf673&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n早前，美國共和黨眾議員Mike Gallagher出席一個智庫視象訪問嘅時候，談論到香港，節錄喺下面，有幾點值得留意：<br />\n<br />\n&gt; 香港人可能會好似新疆維吾爾族人咁，被送去集中營<br />\n&gt; 六四可能會發生喺香港 ( Tiananmen-like purge 天安門式清洗)<br />\n&gt; 佢認為要盡力救香港人<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n另外，眾議員 Mike Gallagher 所講嘅，同先前共和黨參議員 Ben Sasse 選擇六四正日首讀庇護簽證法案，都係指向同一個方向：香港發生六四嘅可能性<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/shocked.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/shocked.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/shocked.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n但 Mike Gallagher 準備提出嘅建議，係同先前提出嘅庇護簽證法案唔一樣，依個建議係向香港人發出難民簽證，而美國一向對難民簽證都有年度配額，申請人要喺美國境外，並且每年由總統決定配額，但庇護簽證就無年度配額，申請人要喺美國境內，而自從侵侵上台之後，佢就將個難民配額降到好低<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/arrested.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n當然，法案入面可以增加條文繞過總統去調高個配額，尤其係依位議員呼籲要盡力救香港人，甚至其實可以加入條文，畀香港人配額豁免權，無上限接收任何有香港身分證嘅人，雖然依個可能性好低，但個重點係，美國議員先後明示暗示，香港有可能發生六四，咁我地應該點面對好呢<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/wail.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n(PS：個訪問係6月8號，但前日22號先擺上網)<br />\n<br />\nWhile the world was shocked at the brutality of the Chinese regime in 1989, no one can claim surprise today, which is why the looming National Security Law in Hong Kong is so troubling. It&rsquo;s a flagrant violation of the &rsquo;84 Sino-British Joint Declaration and the Hong Kong Basic Law. It seems as though they&rsquo;re trying to extinguish the last flame of independence in Hong Kong. And, of course, look at the concentration camps in Xinjiang and forced labor of Uyghur Muslims to understand the fate that could befall a Hong Kong democracy activist and anyone the party deems insufficiently loyal.<br />\n<br />\nSo, final thing I&rsquo;d say, as we reflect on Tiananmen and the nature of this ideological competition, again, this is an area where there&rsquo;s an effort in Congress to do some solid bipartisan work alongside my colleague John Curtis, what we&rsquo;re calling a Hong Kong airlift to provide priority refugee status to Hongkongers facing CCP persecution. We&rsquo;re working through the details right now, but with the potential <span style=\"color: red;\">Tiananmen-like purge looming</span>, I think we need to step up and save as many Hongkongers as possible. I was encouraged to see British Prime Minister Boris Johnson suggest something similar.<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong is one of the most educated populations in the world with high-tech skills, love of freedom, hatred of CCP, and any nation would be lucky to have Hongkongers. And so I think that&rsquo;s one thing that we can do.<br />\n<br />\n=====傳送門=====<br />\n訪問：<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.hudson.org/research/16163-transcript-congressman-mike-gallagher-on-the-importance-of-strategic-alliances-amid-chinese-communist-aggression\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hudson.org%2Fresearch%2F16163-transcript-congressman-mike-gallagher-on-the-importance-of-strategic-alliances-amid-chinese-communist-aggression&d=91nyg34XrGq4aGOua7i4Jem6EOSy25kVi46SvbSXLY8%3D&h=8ba65221\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.hudson.org/research/16163-transcript-congressman-mike-gallagher-on-the-importance-of-strategic-alliances-amid-chinese-communist-aggression</a><br />\n<br />\n美國《香港庇護簽證法案》已通過參議院首讀<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/2053805\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/2053805</a>"},{"pid":"861fa81a04952408f8be0cd9